Pictures stolen from antiques shop

Paintings valued at nearly ?8,000 were stolen from an antiques shop in 
Long Melford.
The two framed oil paintings were taken from Long Melford Antiques 
Centre, in Little St Mary's, at around 2.45am on Saturday, April 28.

The store was broken into via the roof and even though the burglars 
triggered the alarm, they still made off with the pictures.

The paintings are a pair, measuring 94x77cm (landscape) and are of 
battle scenes. They are very dark, possibly by a Russian artist and are 
in two-inch black wooden slightly patterned frames.

Anyone with information should contact Pc Niall Johnson at Sudbury 
Police Station on 01473 613500 or Crime Stoppers on 0800 555 111.

http://www.sudburytoday.co.uk




